quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  21,25,"And We sent never a Messenger before thee except that We revealed to him, saying, 'There is no god but I; so serve Me"
  21,26,"They say:' 'The All-merciful has taken to Him a son.' Glory be to Him! Nay, but they are honoured servants"
  21,27,"that outstrip Him not in speech, and perform as He commands"
  21,28,"He knows what is before them and behind them, and they intercede not save for him with whom He is well-pleased, and they tremble in awe of Him"
  21,29,"If any of them says, 'I am a god apart from Him', such a one We recompense with Gehenna; even so We recompense the evildoers"
  21,30,"Have not the unbelievers then beheld that the heavens and the earth were a mass all sewn up, and then We unstitched them and of water fashioned every living thing? Will they not believe"
  21,31,"And We set in the earth firm mountains lest it should shake with them, and We set in it ravines to serve as ways, that haply so they may be guided"
  21,32,and We set up the heaven as a roof well-protected; yet still from Our signs they are turning away
  21,33,"It is He who created the night and the day, the sun and the moon, each swimming in a sky"
  21,34,"We have not assigned to any mortal before thee to live forever; therefore, if thou diest, will they live forever"
  21,35,"Every soul shall taste of death; and We try you with evil and good for a testing, then unto Us you shall be returned"